Data: Mortaza to Warner, 1 run short and wide, he cuts firmly to deep cover-point
Mortaza to Finch, 1 run 114kph, slower ball, on leg, he tucks this behind square
Mortaza to Warner, no run back of a length on off, he defends off the back foot
Mortaza to Warner, 1 run 120kph, back of a length on off, he turns this behind square with control
Mortaza to Finch, no run 126kph, back of a length angled in, he sits back and punches straight to cover
Mortaza to Finch, FOUR runs 114kph, angled down leg and Finch just glances this fine for four! Bad ball and easy pickings for Finch
Shakib to Warner, no run flatter on off, he defends from the crease
Shakib to Warner, 1 run tossed up, he skips down and drives neatly to long on
Shakib to Finch, 1 run round arm, drifting in, he mistimes a drive trying to go through the off side, drags it straight of midwicket to long on
Shakib to Warner, 3 runs shorter outside off, he punches this and threads it between cover and mid off, Sabbir has a long chase and does well to haul it in
Shakib to Finch, 1 run skips down early, it's darted in, he stands up and punches down to long on
Shakib to Warner, 1 run tossed up on middle, he drives easily to long on
Rubel to Warner, no run 134kph, back of a length, fourth stump, he cuts off the back foot straight to backward point
Rubel to Warner, 1 run 135kph, back of a length wide of off, he cuts off the back foot to deep point
Rubel to Finch, 1 run 136kph, back of a length, fourth stump, he stays leg side and drives off the back foot, opening the face to get it to deep cover-point
Rubel to Warner, 2 runs 136kph, short ball, and he pulls to midwicket but Soumya misfields, it's a long chase for Shakib but he cuts it off
Rubel to Warner, no run 138kph, good length angled across, he flashes and misses. There's a huge roar from the crowd but no edge. He pinned the ears back there
Rubel to Warner, 1 run full wide half volley, hint of tail away, he plays a strong square drive but straight to the sweeper at deep cover-point

Shakib to Warner, FOUR runs full toss and he skips out and drives beautifully inside out past cover! Very good placement. He didn't try and over hit it, just used his feet to get there on the full and placed it well
Shakib to Warner, SIX runs Bang! Slog sweep way back over midwicket! Now he's going. That was in the slot, he got down on one knee and launched it 94m with the turn. Huge hit
Shakib to Warner, no run shorter length, he's back and punching straight to cover
Shakib to Warner, no run slight leading edge, closing the face trying to work to leg
Shakib to Warner, no run clips this straight to midwicket
Shakib to Warner, 1 run slower on leg, he sits back and works this deftly into the gap at square leg
Rubel to Warner, no run 141kph, back of a length, leg stump, takes him on the thigh pad trying to work it behind square
Rubel to Warner, 1 run back of a length, 128kph, cutter, he punches off the back foot to deep cover-point
Rubel to Finch, no run full angled into off, he drives firmly back to the bowler
Rubel to Finch, 1 run 136kph, back of a length, on off, he's back and working this wide of midwicket
Rubel to Warner, no run 135kph, good length on leg, he defends on the front foot to midwicket
Rubel to Warner, 1 run short into the ribs, 136kph, he's back and pulling this neatly to fine leg. Fourth time Warner has reached 50 in the World Cup.
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 wide drifting way down the leg side and called
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run drifting a long way into leg, no turn, he's back and knocking this to square leg
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, no run tossed up on off, he drives straight back to the bowler
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, no run flatter on off, he's back and punching back to the bowler
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, SIX runs slog sweep over square! Just lobbed into his arc on leg, he was down on one knee and lifting this up over square leg into the crowd!

Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, FOUR runs Huge hit that goes too high to clear the rope into the wind at deep midwicket! It half volleyed into the rope. Anywhere else on the ground it was six. Again tossed up in the arc and he just launched it but hit it too high
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, no run flatter outside off, he punches off the back foot to point
Rubel to Warner, no run 138kph, full on off, he pushes on the front foot to cover
Rubel to Warner, no run back of a length outside off, he pushes off the back foot to backward point
Rubel to Warner, 2 runs back of a length, 139kph, on the hip, he's back quickly and tucking this behind square, into the big gap and they run two to bring up the century stand
Rubel to Warner, no run 136kph, rears off a length and hits him flush on the glove! Wow that climbed. He has broken that bottom left thumb before like that
Rubel to Warner, 1 run short into the ribs, he pulls through square leg, he didn't time it
Rubel to Finch, no run length ball on the stumps, pushed back towards the bowler off the back foot

Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run length ball on the stumps, Warner comes down the track and looks to work it towards mid-on, misses and is rapped on the pads. A big appeal for lbw but given not out. Was probably going down with the drift
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run length ball around off, pushes it towards covers
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run length ball on the stumps, Warner goes back and forces it towards long-on
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, 1 run length again, spinning into Finch who gives himself some room and eases it towards long-on for a walking single
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run length around off, flatter at 91kph, Warner defends it from the front foot, bat and pad close
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run length around off, a bit of room this time, punched through covers off the back foot
Rubel to Warner, no run short of length on middle and leg, goes for the pull and misses, struck on the thigh
Rubel to Warner, no run length ball around middle and off, Warner stays leg side of the ball and taps it towards cover
Rubel to Warner, 1 run short of length on the stumps, a bit of extra bounce, Warner adjusts well to pull it towards fine leg, rolling his wrists over
Rubel to Finch, 1 run short of length outside off, punched off the back foot towards the left of the mid-off
Rubel to Warner, 1 wide down the leg side, Warner goes for the pull but too wide to connect
Rubel to Warner, 1 wide short of length but once again drifting down the leg side, another wide
Rubel to Warner, no run better from Rubel, similar length but this time into the body, Warner is cramped is he looks to swat it away
Rubel to Warner, 2 runs length ball around middle and off, Warner dabs it towards covers, a bit of fumble there allows an extra run
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, no run length ball around off, flatter in trajectory, Finch waits on the back foot and guides towards point
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, 2 runs backs away to the fuller delivery and looks to go aerial, mistimed towards wide long-on for a couple
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, no run flatter on the stumps, pushed back towards the bowler this time
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, FOUR runs down the leg side and Finch manages to get some bat on it, and that's another fifty for Australia captain. his eighth in last 11 innings
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Finch, 1 run fuller on the stumps and pushed towards long-on
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run length ball around off, comes forward and defends it back towards the bowler
Soumya to Finch, no run starts with a gentle one, a touch fuller around off, Finch comes forward and drives it towards extra cover
Soumya to Finch, 1 run length ball but on the stumps this time, driven towards long-on for an easy single
Soumya to Warner, 2 runs a slower one but fuller around off, Warner drives it past extra cover but sweeper comes across to keep it to two
Soumya to Warner, 1 run fuller and wider, Warner reaches out for it and steers it towards sweeper cover

Soumya to Finch, OUT against the run of play, Soumya strikes in his first over. Was a length ball around off, Finch was looking to run it down but is surprised by the extra bounce. He checks his shot but ends up hitting it straight into the hands of short third man. Bangladesh have a breakthrough finally
Soumya to Khawaja, no run fuller around off, Khawaja comes forward and pushes it towards cover-point
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run length ball around off and angling in with the arm, pushes it towards mid-off
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, no run fuller around off, turns it towards short midwicket
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run length ball around off, taps it towards long-on to get off the mark
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run fuller around off, comes forward and pushes it back towards the bowler
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run fuller again, Warner gives himself some room and drives but once again straight towards Mehidy
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run short of length outside off, goes back and cuts it away but cannot beat extra cover
Soumya to Khawaja, no run length around off and middle, pushes it towards mid-off
Soumya to Khawaja, no run length around off, comes forward and pushes it towards point, another dot
Soumya to Khawaja, no run a touch fuller and wider, Khawaja looks to drive it through covers but the ball comes slower off the wicket and takes the inner half of the bat
Soumya to Khawaja, no run pitched up around off, driven off the front foot but straight towards mid-off
Soumya to Khawaja, 1 leg bye a huge shout for lbw but probably pitched outside leg. Was an offcutter on a length, Khawaja was moving across and looks to glance, misses. Gets a leg bye though
Soumya to Warner, 1 run length ball around off, punches towards the right of mid-off from the back foot

Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 2 runs length ball around off, punched off the back foot towards deep point, sprints back for the second, no one better than in world cricket probably than Warner in spotting twos
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run uses his feet this time to drive it towards long-on
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, no run length ball around off, stays back and pushes it towards extra cover
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 2 runs fuller this time, around off and Khawaja drives it towards deep extra cover, comes back for the second
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run a bit of hesitation but done safely in the end, length ball on middle and angling in, pushes it past short midwicket
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run short of length outside off, goes back and cuts it towards deep point
Soumya to Warner, no run length ball outside off, Warner cuts it hard but a diving stop at backward point diving to his left
Soumya to Warner, no run back of length around off, pushes it gently towards mid-off
Soumya to Warner, 1 run back of length and angling across, Warner once again stays back, punches it towards covers for a quick single
Soumya to Khawaja, 2 runs length ball around off, drives it through covers for a couple of runs more
Soumya to Khawaja, FOUR runs short of length on middle and leg, Khawaja pulls it stylishly behind square leg, focusing on the placement than power and gets a four
Soumya to Khawaja, no run length ball around off, pushes it towards covers
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run length ball at the batsman, 91 kph, Warner goes back and cuts but straight towards the bowler
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run fuller around off and middle, drives it towards wide long-off for one

Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run a mix-up there as Warner was ball-watching for a moment, but realises soon that he has to sprint, a fumble by Sabbir Rahman at mid-on helps as well. Was a fuller delivery that Kahwaja pushed down the track while coming down the track
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run flatter around off, punched off the back foot towards covers
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run works this fuller delivery towards long-off for one
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run length ball around off, pushes it towards mid-off for one
Soumya to Warner, 1 run slower one on middle and leg, Warner opens the face of the bat to work it towards sweeper cover
Soumya to Khawaja, 1 run length ball on the pads, flicked away towards deep square leg
Soumya to Warner, 1 run length ball on middle and leg, tucked away towards midwicket
Soumya to Khawaja, no run length ball around middle, pushes it towards mid-on
Soumya to Khawaja, 1 run length ball outside off, comes forward and drives it on the up towards long-off
Soumya to Warner, 1 run another offcutter on the pads, flicked towards midwicket, Warner was looking for the second initially but decides against it as the fielder charges towards the ball
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run flatter on middle and leg, turns it towards short midwicket
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run fuller around off, digs it out towards the right of long-off
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run fuller around off, drives it towards long-off for another single
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run fuller on middle and leg, drives it inside out towards long-off and picks up another single
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run length ball on the pads, flicked away towards deep square leg
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run length ball angling on the pads, Warner goes for the flick but cannot beat short fine leg
Soumya to Khawaja, 1 run length ball around off, drives it on the up towards deep extra cover
Soumya to Warner, FOUR runs fuller around off, in the slot for Warner who clears his front leg and lofts it over extra cover and moves into 80s
Soumya to Warner, 1 run length ball on the stumps, pushed towards long-on to keep the scoreboard ticking
Soumya to Khawaja, 1 run fuller around off, drives it on the move towards long-off

Soumya to Warner, FOUR runs short of length outside off, enough room for Warner to rock back and cut it past the point fielder, beats the sweeper cover as well. Surely, this has to be the last over for Soumya
Soumya to Warner, 1 run cutter on middle and leg, pulls it towards backward square leg and keeps the strike
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run fuller on the stumps, comes forward and pushes it towards long-off
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run length ball around off, drives i square off the wicket, deep point cuts it off
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run length ball on the stumps, backs away and opens the face of the bat to work it towards deep point
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, no run fuller around off, pushes it towards extra cover from the crease

Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, no run fuller around off, looks to smash it away but the ball is not coming on to the bat easily, ends up hitting on to his shoe. Was looking for a single as the ball rolled towards cover-point but Warner wisely sends him back
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, no run flatter and quicker around off, Khawaja was on the back foot, does well to get his bat down in time
Shakib to Warner, 1 run short of length on the stumps, goes down and pulls it towards deep backward square leg
Shakib to Khawaja, no run flatter outside off, goes for the reverse sweep but ends up hitting it low on to the keeper's pad
Shakib to Khawaja, 2 runs another reverse sweep, this time gets it behind point for a couple
Shakib to Khawaja, 1 run short of length around off, goes back and punches it towards sweeper cover
Shakib to Warner, 1 run length ball on the pads, tucked away towards square leg
Shakib to Khawaja, FOUR runs fuller down the leg side, goes for the sweep and gets it fine, beating the man at short fine leg
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, FOUR runs short of length outside off, rocks back and cuts it towards short third man, Mustafizur puts in the dive but cannot prevent the boundary
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, no run fuller around off, uses his feet but pings it straight towards extra cover
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run flatter, angling in towards the batsman who backs away and cuts it towards sweeper cover
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run length ball on the stumps, drives it towards sweeper cover
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 3 runs moves to 99 with that three, was fuller and he drives it towards deep extra cover
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, no run fuller around off, drives but cannot get it past mid-off
Shakib to Warner, no run fuller on the pads, tucked away towards short midwicket

Shakib to Warner, 1 run a touch shorter, Warner gets back and works it behind square and gets to his 16th ODI hundred, the second of this World Cup. Yes, he started slowly but it's not an easy wicket and since he's set, he can accelerate
Shakib to Khawaja, 1 run fuller around off, reverse sweeps it towards short third man for a quick single
Shakib to Warner, no run length ball on the stumps, taps it towards short midwicket
Shakib to Warner, 1 run fuller on the stumps, uses his feet to drive it towards long-on
Shakib to Khawaja, 1 run dragged short this time, Khawaja goes back and pulls it towards deep square leg
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 2 runs fuller around off, and driven firmly towards sweeper cover, the deep point fielder cuts it off
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run length ball on the stumps, works it towards long-on
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run length around off, punched off the back foot towards extra cover
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run length ball on the pads, tucked away towards deep midwicket
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Warner, 1 run short of length outside off, cuts it towards deep backward point
Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Khawaja, 1 run fuller around off, comes forward and drives it towards sweeper cover
Mortaza to Khawaja, 1 run length ball on the stumps, was looking to turn it on the leg side, gets a leading edge that beats extra cover
Mortaza to Warner, no run length ball around off and middle, but Warner finds point with the cut
Mortaza to Warner, FOUR runs short of length this time and with Mashrafe's pace, Warner had enough time to rock back and pull it over midwicket for four
Mortaza to Warner, 1 run slower one this time, fuller on the stumps, drives it towards midwicket for a quick single
Mortaza to Khawaja, FOUR runs another short one from Mashrafe, outside off, Khawaja picks it up and pulls it towards that vacant deep midwicket area
Mortaza to Khawaja, 1 run length ball around off, Khawaja uses his wrists to turn it towards backward square leg
Rubel to Khawaja, 1 run length ball on the pads, hurries on to the batsman but Khawaja works it towards fine leg for one
Rubel to Warner, 1 run short of length outside off, chops it towards mid-off for one
Rubel to Khawaja, 1 run short of length once again, Khawaja swivels to pull it towards deep square leg
Rubel to Warner, no run length ball on middle and leg, no room for Warner there, tucked away towards short midwicket
Rubel to Warner, no run short of length, hitting the Warner in the box off an inside edge as he goes for the pull, he's down but all looks well. Ready to face the next ball
Rubel to Warner, 1 run length ball on the stumps, driven down the ground for a single
Mustafizur to Warner, 1 run 123kph, slower ball wide of off, he cuts, mistiming wide of cover to the sweeper
Mustafizur to Khawaja, no run 133kph, full outside off, he drives flowingly on the up but cover makes a good stop
Mustafizur to Khawaja, 1 run glorious cover drive races to the sweeper in the deep. He hit too well. Hit it too square
Mustafizur to Warner, 1 leg bye 131kph, full angled down leg, it comes off pad and rolls for a leg bye
Mustafizur to Khawaja, 1 run short ball, he stands up and cracks a pull shot, rolling the wrists to get it to deep midwicket

Mustafizur to Warner, 2 runs 122kph, short ball on off, he's cramped, staying leg side he slaps this off the back foot over cover for a couple. Inventive but he couldn't get it straight enough to find the rope
Rubel to Khawaja, 1 run short ball, he hammers a pull shot to the man in the deep, it travels at a warp speed and causes a misfield but it doesn't cost anything
Rubel to Warner, FOUR runs magnificent late cut wide of third man! It was 140kph, short but not that wide, he created some room and late cut it wide of third man and it raced away
Rubel to Warner, 1 run he charges a 141kph length, chops it off the bottom edge to backward point
Rubel to Khawaja, FOUR runs lovely pull shot off the hip! Fractionally short on leg, he lifted the front leg, Brian Lara style and pulled it wide of short fine leg
Rubel to Khawaja, 1 run slower ball back of a length, he works this off the hip behind square. 50 for Khawaja at a run-a-ball. He's played well
Rubel to Warner, 1 run 138kph, skidding through, he grunts as it stays low and he pulls awkwardly behind square
Mustafizur to Warner, no run big swing and miss and it just goes past leg stump! He tried to line this up and launch a length ball straight down the ground but missed
Mustafizur to Warner, FOUR runs thumped over mid off! Banged in back of a length, he backed away and slapped it flat and just over mid off inside the circle. Hit with amazing power
Mustafizur to Warner, 1 bye slower ball bouncer, he tries to cut over point but is cramped and misses, Mushfiqur fumbles behind the stumps on the bounce and they pinch a bye
Mustafizur to Khawaja, no run 135kph, full on leg, he stays leg side and drives very nicely but straight to cover
Mustafizur to Khawaja, no run another slower ball bouncer, brilliantly bowled, it followed Khawaja as he tried to pull and he just got out of the way
Mustafizur to Khawaja, 2 runs slower short ball, it sits up, he hammers a pull shot forward of square into the gap for a couple
Rubel to Warner, 1 wide 141kph, slung short down the leg side and called

Rubel to Warner, SIX runs check drive down the ground the sightscreen! 126kph in the slot and he just checked through the line, picking the slower ball and it went like low golf shot under the wind straight down the ground
Rubel to Warner, 2 runs on the hip, he works this behind square and sprints two. Great running
Rubel to Warner, 1 run short on the hip again, he mistimes a pull behind square to wide fine leg
Rubel to Khawaja, 1 run good length on middle, he works it through midwicket, they look for two but it's not on
Rubel to Warner, 1 run slower ball on leg, he bunts this into midwicket
Rubel to Khawaja, 1 run shorter slower ball, he's back and working this through square leg
Shakib to Khawaja, no run this was fired down leg, would have been a wide, but Khawaja swept it straight to short fine! A mistake there
Shakib to Khawaja, 2 runs low full toss, he clips this wide of long on for a couple
Shakib to Khawaja, 1 run another short ball down leg, again it would have been a wide, he pulls it straight to short fine leg again! Gets one this time
Shakib to Warner, FOUR runs a switch hit up and over short third man! He set up early and it was in the slot outside off, he deliberately lifted it up and over and one bounce four
Shakib to Warner, no run short ball down leg, he pulls again to short fine leg. This would have been a wide as well
Shakib to Warner, SIX runs smacked 20 rows back over deep midwicket! This begged to be hit. A drag down short ball on leg, he set his base and clubbed it miles over deep midwicket

Mustafizur to Khawaja, FOUR runs low full toss outside off, a bottom edge just gets past the keeper! Attempted wide yorker, he got a thin edge that rolled low and wide of Mushfiqur and third man is up.
Mustafizur to Khawaja, FOUR runs clever upper cut! Short slower ball wide of off, Khawaja adjusted well and just lifted it over a vacant slips with no third man back
Mustafizur to Khawaja, 2 runs 132kph, thigh high full toss, he whips this behind square and they run well to get two
Mustafizur to Khawaja, FOUR runs low full toss whipped forward of square! Another bad ball, Khawaja hit this a touch harder than the last one, timed it well to find the rope
Mustafizur to Khawaja, FOUR runs pulled behind square! Fine leg went finer for some reason, this was chest high, he rolled the wrists on a pull and placed it to the rope!
Mustafizur to Khawaja, 1 run low full toss, he glances this straight to the man at fine leg
Mortaza to Khawaja, 1 run 123kph, low full toss, he drives down to long on
Mortaza to Warner, SIX runs full toss swiped over deep midwicket! Right in the strike zone and he clubbed it flat over midwicket and got all of it
Mortaza to Warner, 1 run 126kph, yorker on leg, he digs this out to long on. 150 for Warner! His 6th score 150 plus in ODIs
Mortaza to Khawaja, FOUR runs stunning square drive on the up through point! Wasn't a bad ball, slower ball wide of off, he steered it with amazing timing behind point. Class batting
Mortaza to Khawaja, 1 run good length on off, he drives inside out to deep cover point
Mortaza to Warner, 1 run 126kph, knee high full toss, he tries to launch over midwicket but miscues, getting it to the man in the deep on the bounce
Rubel to Warner, 1 leg bye attempted switch hit to a 139kph, full ball outside leg! It comes off pad for a leg bye
Rubel to Khawaja, 1 run 140kph low full toss on leg, he glances this to wide fine leg
Rubel to Warner, FOUR runs lofted flat and wide of long on! An attempted yorker was a half volley on leg stump, it was in the arc and he shovelled it wide of long on
Rubel to Warner, FOUR runs backs away and upper cuts over short third man! Predicted the short ball, gave room and ramped it over short third man
Rubel to Warner, 2 runs good yorker outside leg, he tried to give room but digs it out through midwicket and sprints two
Rubel to Warner, 1 run 137kph, full on leg stump, he clips this firmly along the ground to deep midwicket
Soumya to Warner, FOUR runs wide full toss, he reaches out and slaps it through point! He had backed away, it was well wide of off, he reached out at full stretched and cracked it

Soumya to Warner, OUT lobs a catch to short third man! Soumya does it again! 115kph short slower ball, Warner tries to upper cut but there's no pace, he just lobs a catch to the man on the circle and Rubel takes an easy catch.
Soumya to Maxwell, 2 runs 116kph, length ball on off, he sits back and works this neatly to the gap at midwicket and they call two straight away. Good running
Soumya to Maxwell, 1 run 123kph, full and straight, he drives easily down to long on
Soumya to Khawaja, 1 run 126kph, low full toss on middle, he steps across his stumps and works it through square leg
Soumya to Maxwell, FOUR runs wide yorker and he steers it behind point! Good delivery but Maxwell's talent and sublime hands steered it past the fielder at pace and it raced to the rope
Rubel to Khawaja, (no ball) 1 run over-steps! 138kph low full toss, whipped to midwicket but what a mistake with the front foot

Rubel to Maxwell, SIX runs What a shot over mid off! Full and wide of off, he had gone outside off, had to adjust and shovel it off the back foot over mid off and into the rope on the full! That is staggering skill
Rubel to Maxwell, FOUR runs carved through cover! Wowee! In the slot wide of off, he cleared the front leg and rifled it through cover!
Rubel to Maxwell, SIX runs clubbed over square leg! You van't bowl a length slower ball to Maxi. He sat and waited and clubbed it over square leg into the crowd
Rubel to Maxwell, no run yorker length, he gives room and steers it to the fielder at cover
Rubel to Maxwell, 3 runs launched into the biggest corner of the ground at wide long on, it's a huge hit down there, Tamim makes the diving save on the rope but they run well enough to get three

Rubel to Khawaja, FOUR runs backs away and slices this through backward point! Elegance, timing, pure class to get a ball from leg stump through backward point. He opened his chest up and the flow of the bat was superb
Soumya to Maxwell, SIX runs chest high short ball slapped over deep midwicket! Bad ball at that pace. Maxwell had all the time in the world to set up and hit the pull shot over deep midwicket

Soumya to Maxwell, OUT a mix up and Maxwell is run out! Full yorker on leg, he got it between his legs to short fine leg and ran, Khawaja started to run and called no! They were both standing mid pitch. Rubel, took his time, fired and hit! Maxwell could not believe Khawaja stopped running!
Soumya to Stoinis, no run 126kph, short and wide, he late cuts straight to short third man
Soumya to Stoinis, 1 run 122kph, full on off, he drives neatly to and conventionally to long off

Soumya to Khawaja, OUT caught behind! Soumya has been unbelievable! A surprise short ball, it comes off the pitch slowly, he tries to pull but is through the shot, gets a bottom edge off the toe of the bat, and Mushfiqur dives forward to take the catch!
Soumya to Smith, 1 run 124kph, perfect yorker, tailing in late into leg stump, he just jams it out and gets one

Mustafizur to Smith, OUT plumb LBW! Smith reviews for the sake of it but it was a full toss that hit him on the shin in front of middle. This is out. No bat. Ball tracking has it hitting the base of middle and off. The review is wasted. He went back and across and tried to whip it behind square and missed it.
Mustafizur to Carey, 1 run 135kph, full on off, he drives firmly but straight to cover. He picked out the fielder
Mustafizur to Stoinis, 1 run length on leg stump, he clips this off the hip to fine leg
Mustafizur to Carey, 1 run thigh high full toss, 136kph, he sits back and just bunts this down to long on
Mustafizur to Stoinis, 1 run 133kph, low full toss outside off, he drives firmly to long on
Mustafizur to Carey, 1 run 137kph, yorker on leg, he digs this out to long on
Soumya to Carey, 1 run slower ball bouncer, he pulls this along the ground to deep forward square

Australia might have left 20 out there despite superb innings from Khawaja and Finch as well. Maxwell's cameo could have been anything but a mix up and then Khawaja's dismissal stalled their innings late.

2.40pm Innings break Australia post 5 for 381. That's their second highest score in World Cups. It was set up by a sublime innings from David Warner. WATCH - Did you miss David Warner's 166? Catch all the highlights from his 16th ODI hundred (Australia, UK, SEA only)
